# Open the file using ctypes
    fd = open(filepath, "rb")
    lib = ctypes.CDLL(fd.name)
    fd.close()

    # Calculate the MD5 hash
    hasher = hashlib.md5()
    while True:
        # Read 1 MB at a time
        buf = fd.read(1 << 20)
        if not buf:
            break
        hasher.update(buf)
    md5_hash = hasher.hexdigest()

    # Calculate the SHA256 hash
    hasher = hashlib.sha256()
    while True:
        # Read 1 MB at a time
        buf = fd.read(1 << 20)
        if not buf:
            break
        hasher.update(buf)
    sha256_hash = hasher.hexdigest()

    return "MD5 Hash: {}\nSHA256 Hash: {}".format(md5_hash, sha256_hash)
